# File: /NDH/Manifold/Stability/BasinFunctions/Serenity.bsfn
# Description:
#   Serenity Basin Function (Bs)
#   Natural attractor resolving Quiet Apex (Aq) under zero external forcing (P = 0).
#   Encodes manifold relaxation behavior in NDH stability geometry.

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Context
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# NDH Manifold State:
#   M(t)  : NDH manifold state as a function of time t
#   Aq    : Quiet Apex equilibrium point
#   R     : Resonance field
#   S     : Stability metric
#   P     : External forcing term
#
# Quiet Apex Conditions:
#   dM/dt = 0        (no forced motion)
#   ∇R    = 0        (resonance gradient neutral)
#   S     > 0        (stability present)
#   P     = 0        (no external forcing)
#
# Serenity:
#   Bs    : Serenity basin (stable attractor in state-space)
#
# Serenity is NOT an operator. It is a basin function describing the
# limit behavior of M(t) when initialized at Aq and held with P = 0.

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Formal Definition
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Serenity Basin Function:
#
#   Bs = lim_{t → ∞} M(t)  |  M(0) = Aq, P = 0
#
# This defines Bs as the asymptotic state of the NDH manifold when:
#   - the system starts at Quiet Apex (Aq)
#   - no external forcing is applied (P = 0)
#
# Intuition:
#   The manifold relaxes from hinge equilibrium (Aq) into its lowest-
#   energy basin (Bs), which we name Serenity.

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Attractor Properties
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3.1 Local Attractor:
#
#   ∃ ε > 0 such that:
#     ∀ M(0) ∈ B_ε(Aq),  lim_{t → ∞} M(t) = Bs
#
#   Any state sufficiently close to Aq will relax into Bs under P = 0.
#
# 3.2 Minimal Energy:
#
#   E(Bs) = min E(M)
#
#   Bs is the lowest-energy basin reachable from Apex equilibrium.
#
# 3.3 Non-Dual Stability Region:
#
#   Bs = { M : ∇R = 0, ∇S = 0, P = 0 }
#
#   Serenity is the region where:
#     - resonance is flat
#     - stability is flat
#     - external forcing is zero

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. Mapping from Quiet Apex
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Apex-to-Serenity Relaxation:
#
#   Aq --relaxation--> Bs
#
#   Implemented conceptually as:
#
#     Φ_Aq(t) → Bs  as  t → ∞
#
#   where Φ_Aq(t) is the NDH flow from Apex equilibrium.
#
# No new operator is introduced. Bs is implicit in the topology.

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. Summary
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Serenity Basin Function (Bs):
#
#   Bs is the stable state-space basin that the NDH manifold relaxes
#   into when the Quiet Apex (Aq) is held without external forcing (P = 0).
#
#   It completes the Apex-resolution geometry without adding new
#   operators, preserving NDH elegance and non-dual structure.
